annotation.TEXT: Whoa, wasn't expecting a hidden coin block there. However, I assume it's there to allow weaker jumpers to reach that pipe, which does lead to a side area. I'll come back for it in a moment.
This parakoopa here worries me...
I could easily go over the top of the level here, but that wouldn't do me any good, since there's no way back down past this point.

I'm glad I picked up that doughnut earlier, because it looks like I'm going to spend most of my NP here. I'd like to get in close and slash him with my powered-up sword, but the hammer barrage makes that too risky.
Good thing ninjas can duck.
This SML2 map skin makes me want to scream, "Honeycomb! Honeycomb! Me want Honeycomb!"

I don't think I want the stopwatch, though. (Although, maybe it would've been worth grabbing anyway, but I have very few hearts right now. Maybe I should've used Sonia in 7-1 or 7-2 instead, to have more chances to get hearts. Oh, well.)
And thus, the ULTIMATE NINJA GUY has rescued this dog/cat/whatever, and is looking for Koume.
Whoa, geez! On the very edge again! Okay, I seriously need some sort of reference to determine exactly where I am to help me land safely. Oh, the tens digit of my coins should do nicely!

...Or not... Huh. Usually in Crossover, bricks that are attached to the bases of pipes contain coins, but not these ones for some reason. (I can't really call that an inaccuracy though, since those bricks were also breakable in the original game.)
Whoa, right on the edge! Talk about close!
And now, for 7-4, a random Ryu.
Uh, I don't think attacking that guy was a good idea!

Yep, there's the hidden 1-up, and revealing it collected the coin for me. I wonder if that coin was meant to hint at that 1-up on the easy difficulty map, and it was accidentally left in the normal difficulty map by mistake?
Yay, Atari graphics. Now, this level contains a bunch of green springboards, which I have to use to cross giant expanses. Going up!
Huh, for some reason, I was given 200+400 points for each of those parakoopas when I shredded them. (You guys saw the mashed-together "200" and "400" displays, right?)
Gorsh!
Now, down this pipe, is... another bonus room!
Alright, so up next is 8-1! And you might be able to guess what I'm planning on doing there. So, place your votes for who you want to see me use next time!
Huh, what's that? A missile expansion? ...Yep!
The platform above the power up block here has been raised one tile, which is good, because otherwise, tall characters that can't duck jump might not be able to get the power up.
Okay, after dodging that firebar, let's climb down this chute and land on a moving platform.
I wonder what the cap was before (Maybe 30?) and what it is now (Maybe 60?)... I'll see if I can figure that out at some point, unless one of you guys happen to know and tell me.
Alright, with this room decimated, let's head into the next area, which is actually not part of the main area of the level.
Agh, I was a tiny iota too late!
Got him! I was hesitating there to both look for a possible opening to get into melee range, and to make sure he wouldn't jump over my shots, since I had limited ammo.
There's nothing major to the left here that I didn't already show before entering the midair pipe earlier.
Dude! I got the ULTIMATE NINJA GUY!!!
Nailed it!

Okay, this level's just like 5-3, where I have to enter a midair pipe to proceed with the level, or else the level will loop endlessly. And, also, just like in 5-3, Crossover is using back-and-forth platforms instead of the sky bonus style platform...
There's no wind, of course, and I believe this gap has been shrunk a bit to accommodate weaker jumpers.
Cool, a sword power up. Okay, now for this elevator shaft. Normally, all of these elevators move down. However, I guess some of them move up now just to help out weaker jumpers.
Uh, oh. I remember that flying cheepos appear here. But, I also remember that there's an invincibility star just up ahead, so I'm going to try to get that quickly!
I could tell that I had reached the point where Lakitu is supposed to go away, just after he showed up there. So, that's why he didn't toss any spinies, because he was in "leaving" mode.
Alright, it's boss time!
Spring!!! I'm sure Lily White would love this level.
There's a multi-coin block which quickly gets cleaned out. Also, yeah, I know I'm low on time, but I think I'll have enough time to completely clean out this room and still finish... I hope...

Interesting... These two fire bars are spinning the wrong way. However, once again, I'm guessing that's done on purpose, because not everyone can just duck in the corners to avoid them. (I wonder if this'll also be the case in world C-4...)
Oh, man! So many bricks for me to destroy with my AWESOME SPREAD GUN! Mwahahaha!!!

Oh, what's this? There's a loose coin just to the right of the upper row of bricks here which doesn't belong. I'll have to mention this on the ER forums. Oh, and there's a hidden 1-up just below the coin.
All the bricks must die! Including the ones holding up the pipes, which probably contain coins...
Okay, now if I kick the third koopa here to the right, and I'm using a fast character (I'm not), I can potentially get a 1-up combo here.
Uh, oh... Oh, no worries.
To be continued... Yo!
Nice! Let's try screwing up some enemies with this!
Ha, Magikoopa is no match for me! However, these Buzzies and the bullet cannon to the right might be an issue...

Man, I kind of wish at least one of you had voted for someone that could run fast, because this area is designed for giving you a 1-up combo, if you can keep up with the kicked shell. And unfortunately, neither Bill, Samus, Simon, nor Ryu are very fast...
LOL, the end of the victory music got cutoff. Okay, now for 7-2, I believe I'll go with a random Samus.
Same deal with that red springboard, to keep a weaker jumper from potentially getting stranded on that platform.

Huh. Not many votes this time, so I guess I'll be using these four today. Now, there was an alt. skin vote for Sonia (Simon), and a vote for me to use Ryu in 7-4, so I'll go with those. But, for 7-1, I believe I'll go with a random Bill skin.
There's a hidden power up block here, above this fire bar.
So, sadly, that means no 1-up combo for me here. Oh, well.
Okay, the flagpole is shortly after this bullet cannon, so I should have just enough time to try for six fireworks...
Hello, and welcome back to SMB Crossover! Up above are the voting results this time.
Awesome! Also, fortunately, I guess this brick walkway up here was changed to hold coin blocks, to prevent me from stranding myself, so that's pretty nice.
I got the suitless version of the SNES Samus.
Okay, here's the goal, so let's try for six fireworks as usual.
Yeah, I'm not taking that "L". However, I will go back here and enter this pipe now.
Actually, I landed that perfectly! So, I guess that fire bar wasn't really a big deal after all.
Okay, it takes about 13 whip swings at that rhythm before I land. Knowing this could be helpful to me.
No, I don't want the Ice Beam. I prefer the Wave Beam.

Oh, man. More fire bars. Yeah, maybe I should've used Sonia in 7-2 and Samus here. However, these shouldn't be too tricky, since there's no wind to blow me around in Crossover. (Normally, there would be wind for almost the entirety of this level.)
I got a sunburned Lance this time. Alright, now let's start blasting stuff with my AWESOME SPREAD GUN!
Splut!
Alright, for Spring Yard Zone... Er, I mean 7-3, let's go with Sonia Belmont.
Wow, really? Not a single missile drop from any of those bricks?

Oh, and just like in 5-3, I can backtrack there in Crossover, but I checked this later, and it doesn't let me triple-dip on the first power up block. Okay, now I know a low-flying Lakitu is coming up here...
Yeah, Haggleman's attacks hit faster. Just pointing that out.
GAAAMMMEEE!!! Of course, it would decide not to have the koopa fall into the gap the one time that it matters most. I wouldn't have been able to get a 1-up, but I could've gotten some combo points.
Ooh, doughnut. Also, all of the enemies down there are normally Buzzies, but I guess the first six got changed to green koopas to allow non-plumber characters to always be able to beat them.
Whoa, that's a bullet cannon! I'm lucky it didn't fire at a bad time for me there!
Whoa. Gotta watch out for Bowser's fire when making these jumps.
HAHAHAHAHA!!! Oh, that was perfect! I totally sniped that Lakitu before it had a chance to do anything!
There's the pipe I'll need to enter. However, just like back in 5-3, I'm going to go the wrong way once. Also, I wonder if this'll let me double-dip on the power up again...
Well, let's see if I can find some missiles around here...
Huh, there's a red springboard there, probably to help weaker jumpers reach the pipe.
BOING!!!
Please tell me that I can safely duck in this corner here... Oh, I don't even have to duck. That's good.
Alright, let's move, move, move!
Ooh, I'll certainly take that "R".
Oh, and since I have the Varia, I can totally ignore these fire bars! Nice!
Okay, the goal is just up ahead, but the fire bar might impede my timing here...
Wow, I'm glad I can safely hang out in the upper corner there!
Yep! Ooh, what have we here?
